hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Looking for a job stark medical law The solution is fairly simple. Chris Grayling, the Justice Secretary, is planning a British Bill of Rights that would be senior to any jurisdiction from Strasbourg. We have never, before, needed a constitution – such basic principles as press freedom have been taken for granted. When the Scottish Parliament was granted powers to regulate television, the press was not mentioned: as recently as the late 1990s it was unthinkable that this old liberty would be extinguished. Yet next week, the Privy Council will consider government plans to do just that.
